  "text": "Osteoclasts express TRAP, an enzyme, which can be identified in cells through a histochemical staining methodology [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Staining solution (Sigma Diagnostics) was made up of acetate, naphthol AS-BI phosphoric acid and tartrate solution in 371C water and fast garnet GBC salt was added to the solution. This solution was filtered and the slides were then incubated in the solution for 1 h at 371C and then washed in water.",
